<%- include('./partials/header') %>

<div class="row mb-4">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-center mb-4">Money Management Tips</h2>
        
        <div class="alert alert-primary">
          <div class="d-flex">
            <div class="me-3">
              <i class="fas fa-info-circle fa-2x"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="alert-heading">Smart Money Management</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">Use these practical tips to better manage your pocket money and build healthy financial habits.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row mt-4">
          <!-- 50/30/20 Rule -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-primary tip-card primary-tip">
              <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-chart-pie me-2"></i>The 50/30/20 Rule</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>A simple budgeting method to allocate your pocket money:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>50%</strong> for needs (food, transportation)</li>
                  <li><strong>30%</strong> for wants (entertainment, eating out)</li>
                  <li><strong>20%</strong> for savings and debt repayment</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">This flexible framework helps ensure you're covering essentials while still enjoying life and building savings.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Tracking Expenses -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-success tip-card success-tip">
              <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-search-dollar me-2"></i>Track Every Expense</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>Record all expenses, no matter how small:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Use this app to log expenses immediately</li>
                  <li>Categorize properly (food, travel, etc.)</li>
                  <li>Review your spending patterns weekly</li>
                  <li>Identify and eliminate unnecessary expenses</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">You can't manage what you don't measure. Tracking helps you understand where your money goes.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Cash Envelope System -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-warning tip-card warning-tip">
              <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-envelope me-2"></i>Cash Envelope System</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>A practical method to control spending:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>Create envelopes for different expense categories</li>
                  <li>Allocate cash to each envelope at the start of the week/month</li>
                  <li>Only spend what's in the envelope for each category</li>
                  <li>When an envelope is empty, stop spending in that category</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">This tangible approach creates a physical limit to your spending and prevents overspending.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- No-Spend Challenge -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-danger tip-card danger-tip">
              <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-ban me-2"></i>No-Spend Challenge</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>Boost your savings with periodic challenges:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Designate a day, weekend, or week as "no-spend" time</li>
                  <li>Only spend on absolute necessities during this period</li>
                  <li>Find free alternatives for entertainment</li>
                  <li>Transfer the money you would have spent to savings</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">These challenges help break spending habits and show you how much you can save when you're mindful.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- 24-Hour Rule -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-info tip-card info-tip">
              <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-clock me-2"></i>The 24-Hour Rule</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>Combat impulse spending:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Wait 24 hours before making any non-essential purchase</li>
                  <li>For larger purchases, wait a week</li>
                  <li>Ask yourself if you really need it after the waiting period</li>
                  <li>Consider if the item aligns with your financial goals</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">This simple delay helps eliminate emotional purchases and reduces buyer's remorse.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Savings Goals -->
          <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-secondary tip-card">
              <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-bullseye me-2"></i>Set Specific Savings Goals</h5>
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>Make saving more motivating:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Define clear, specific goals (e.g., "Save â‚¹5,000 for new headphones")</li>
                  <li>Break large goals into smaller milestones</li>
                  <li>Set deadlines for each goal</li>
                  <li>Visualize your progress (use progress bars or charts)</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="card-text text-muted mt-2">Specific goals are more motivating than vague ones like "save more money."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="alert alert-success mt-4">
          <div class="d-flex">
            <div class="me-3">
              <i class="fas fa-star fa-2x"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="alert-heading">Quick Daily Tips</h5>
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <ul class="mb-0">
                    <li>Pack lunch instead of eating out</li>
                    <li>Use public transportation or walk when possible</li>
                    <li>Unsubscribe from shopping newsletters to avoid temptation</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <ul class="mb-0">
                    <li>Use student discounts whenever available</li>
                    <li>Compare prices before making purchases</li>
                    <li>Avoid shopping when hungry or emotional</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('./partials/footer') %> 